volume.name: Johnny Boo: The Best Little Ghost in the World

description:
Of the myriad genres comic books ventured into during its golden age, none was as controversial as or came at a greater cost than horror; the public outrage it incited almost destroyed the entire industry. Yet before the watchdog groups and Congress could intercede, horror books were flying off the newsstands. During its peak period (1951-54) over fifty titles appeared each month. Apparently there was something perversely irresistible about these graphic excursions into our dark side, and Four Color Fear collects the finest of these into a single robust and affordable volume.

EC is the comic book company most fans associate with horror; its complete line has been reprinted numerous times, and deservedly so. But to the average reader there remain unseen quite a batch of genuinely disturbing, compulsive, imaginative, at times even touching, horror stories presented from a variety of visions and perspectives, many of which at their best can stand toe to toe with EC.

All of the better horror companies are represented: Ace, Ajax-Farrell, American Comics Group, Avon, Comic Media, Fawcett, Fiction House, Gilmor, Harvey, Quality, Standard, St. John, Story, Superior, Trojan, Youthful and Ziff-Davis. Artist perennials Jack Cole, Reed Crandall, George Evans, Frank Frazetta, Jack Katz, Al Williamson, Basil Wolverton, and Wallace Wood contribute both stories and covers, with many of the 32 full-sized covers created by specialists Bernard Baily, L.B. Cole, William Eckgren, and Matt Fox. (See below for a link to the full Table of Contents.)

Editors John Benson and Greg Sadowski have sifted through hundreds of rare books to cherry-pick the most compelling scripts and art, and they provide extensive background notes on the artists, writers, and companies involved in their creation. Digital restoration has been performed with subtlety and restraint, mainly to correct registration and printing errors, with every effort made to retain the flavor of the original comics, and to provide the reader the experience of finding in the attic a bound volume of the finest non-EC horror covers and stories of the pre-code era.

description: Abner on death row? Also in this volume the introduction of Lonesome Polecat and the wonder potion, Kickapoo Joy Juice. This fifth volume reprints the 1939 daily strips and includes an introduction by Julie Capp Cairol. Also included is an article that puts the strip into the historical context of 1939.

Entering the Maze of Eternity which holds those who made the wrong choice...or no choice, the traveler is led to the very center of Hell and there, the Ruler of Hell awaits. The answer to why the journey was completed is also revealed as the traveler's end is complete.

Contents

  • Maze of Eternity
  • Giants
  • Blasphemers
  • Realm of Ice
  • Dante's Devil
  • Devil's Guises

The first time in print for these digital first adventures!

The Dark Knight battles some of his greatest foes in this oversized adventure!

The Joker’s put a mind-bendingly nefarious plan into effect for the wealthy of Gotham City…

description: Though drugged by a powerful narcotic, THE CISCO KID finally "sees" what happened the night of his TONYA'S murder. Quickly, he plans a violent ambush against the men who stole his life from him those many years ago. He must kill them all, with his only ally being the devil of RAGE that grips his heart and holds his gun hand steady!
name: The Shootout

description: We look back to Rapunzel's first fateful steps as she's shipwrecked on the shores of the Hidden Kingdom. She's charmed by the Celestial Court, but there is political intrigue afoot and a forbidden love affair when Rapunzel falls in love with Tomoko, a kitsune fox spirit. Meanwhile Joel Crow and Jack of Fables get more than they bargained for in a seedy pachinko parlor and karaoke club. And when Rapunzel is reunited with her former lover, she's shocked at the monster Tomoko has become
name: The Hidden Kingdom Chapter Two: Hard-Boiled Wonderland

description: After last issue's surprise announcement, Amazonia has returned to her home dimension of Leandia. And that's not the only thing that's new. Darkblade has sidekicks to train, Amazonia gets a replacement back on Earth, and Abby's bookstore does something it never has before. The baby's not the only change that's coming.

volume.name: Love and Capes: What To Expect

description: Meet Jetpack Cat, Aqua Cat, Rollerskate Cat, and Karate Cat – the astounding Action Cats! When action calls, they answer – unless it’s nap time, or there’s a sunbeam or a particularly active butterfly to catch. No, don’t worry, we mean it, the Action Cats will save the day!

FINAL EXECUTION races to its thrilling conclusion!

X-Force brings the attack to the Brotherhood, but there is dissension in the ranks.

Genesis faces the truth about Apocalypse and his destiny!
name: The Father Who Must Be Killed

description:
It's Domino and Daredevil... but this is not a team-up!

Domino has always been lucky...or maybe the people around her are just unlucky.

Start reading here!
name: The Boneyard, Part 1

description:
The story is about two brothers and a sister in a Central American location. Superman and Wonder Woman rescue one of the brothers from a minefield. The sister is saved from a landmine by Wonder Woman. Superman and Wonder Woman teach the children about the dangers of landmines through signs, posters, and by introducing them to a child who had been a victim of a landmine explosion.

The storyline was recommended by American soldiers who had served in the 1st PSYOP Airborne Battalion as minefield assessors while in Costa Rica, Honduras, and Nicaragua.

Note: Wonder Woman wears a more modest costume for this particular region and audience.
name: The Hidden Killer

volume.name: The Hidden Killer (Superman and Wonder Woman)

description: Behind the scenes look of how, in a typical day and a typical X-Factor case, Pip the Troll holds the entire team together without their knowledge.
name: Short Story

description:
The Kingpin has been murdered! Daredevil has been murdered! And that's just the beginning of the story!

Ben Urich digs deep into the seedy underbelly of the MU & discovers Matt Murdock's biggest secret yet!.

Some of the greatest creators to ever take on the Man Without Fear unite for his final story!
name: Part Two

description:
Series finale! The end of the Defenders!

All your questions answered!

Everybody dies! Everything ends! So how do the good guys pull it off?
name: The Impossible End

description: Horizon Labs take a field trip to the Savage Land! But when has a trip to the Savage Land ever gone right? When a horde of super-powered lizards attack, it’s up to Spider-Man, Devil Dinosaur, and Moon Boy to save the day! Raptors are bad enough, but can Spidey overcome a prehistoric language barrier, too?

MINIMUM CARNAGE PART FOUR! At the will of a madman in the Microverse!

Scarlet Spider must face the monster within to fight the monster of Carnage!

Meanwhile, Venom takes on a mission – and the cost may be more than his life!
name: Minimum Carnage; Part 4; Kill Carnage

description:
FINAL ISSUE!

End-of-an-era Series Finale!

In the aftermath of the grueling “Final Exam”, can friendships, romances – and the Academy itself – survive?
name: Commencement

description: When the remains of The Queen's Gambit are brought to the surface, Moira Queen reflects about her lost loved ones and makes a stunning discovery.
name: Fathoms

description: The King of Oz bestows Button Bright with a cleverly generous gift -- a fox's head! But how will Dorothy and the Shaggy Man get through the Deadly Desert? Johnny Dooit may have an idea!
Why is the government after Iron Man? A mysterious figure from Tony's past returns -- with a vendetta. Plus: the first appearance of War Machine!

Two classic Avengers return for the first time in years to celebrate the end of an era! But does this modern world really need the Avengers?

A giant status quo shift is on the horizon. Watch as the Avengers come to terms with themselves as a team and a family.

PLUS: Hydra with alien tech? Uh oh!
name: Rock the Microverse

description:
Jean Grey finds herself on the run... from Cyclops!

Prophet’s final plan for human survival takes shape.

A weapon that could kill Weapon X, a.k.a. the Overlord, is discovered!
name: Jean Jeanie

description: In this night and in this hour...The years have passed quickly for The Charmed Ones since they learned of their magical heritage. In only one decade they have experienced so much love and loss, joy and sorrow, failure and success. But time marches on and new challenges will be met as Phoebe is haunted by her past, Piper must deal with the present, and Paige is forced to cope with the future. See how season 9 comes to a close!!! Collecting issues 20-24.
name: Volume 4

description: END TIMES continues! The New Avengers are thrown into disarray as one of their deadliest enemies has returned.
name: A Tangled Web

description: The investigation is ongoing and it leads Grom to fight club.
name: Чумной доктор. Часть 2

description: "Archie Marries Betty"-- It's the reunion we've all been waiting for as The Archies reunite to help raise money for a worthy cause. Jellybean's unreliability comes to a head with older brother Jughead after the stress of Midge's pregnancy takes its toll. Conflicts aside, this issue is a can't-miss affair with Josie and the Pussycats making their Life with Archie debut as the headlining act for the grand opening of Archie's new music club.

"Archie Marries Veronica"-- Change is afoot in Riverdale! After the devastating shooting of his partner, Kevin rethinks his risky career path while Clay recuperates. Kevin's not the only one with a career shift in mind as Veronica moves on from Lodge Industries and Riverdale's Mayor Moose contemplates making a political move to the senate. Plus, it's the premiere of Reggie and Betty's reality show at the Chok'lit Shoppe and Jughead is pulling out all the stops to make it a Hollywood-style event! In a night filled with excitement, Kevin has an announcement that will set the scene for many issues to come!

An all-new 4 issue mini series from the Master of Horror. Nicholas Stastny is a saintly lad. He loves his maker, his family, and above all, his animals. He loves 'em to death! Experience the most disturbing story from Bluewater yet as we learn the gruesome truths to becoming a 'Good Boy.'
name: Good Boy

description:
Hell of a Night

Detective Katharine Cavenaugh, after surviving a brutal attack, is hot on the trail of the vicious killer that has been slashing young women to death. Her investigation leads her to an underground club of wannabe vampires. But not all of them may be pretending...
name: Hell of a Night

description:
Black Magic TV

A small, weird western town on the edge of hell is invaded by a horde of demons in the shape of bandits. On their wild rampage through the town, the bandits run afoul of an Asperger's syndrome boy with strange powers, and his silent, giant companion. The boy and the giant defeat the demon-bandits and drive them back into Hell. The boy climbs up on the shoulders of his giant friend and rides off into the sunset, leaving the town's preacher and mayor, who looks suspiciously like VINCENT PRICE, wondering...

The planet Galador rebuilds its elite defense force, recruiting a new generation of Spaceknights! Can Balin and Tristan, the sons of legendary Spaceknight Starshine, live up to the legend of their family name? Collects SPACEKNIGHTS (2000) #1-2.

The newly minted Spaceknight squad uncovers a terrible truth: the Dire Wraiths have returned!

With the might of the Deathwing at their call, the Galadorians' ancient foes are more powerful than ever!

Meanwhile, a triumvirate of alien races bands together to wage war on Galador - but why?

Can young Tristan's prescient visions help uncover the true nature of the Wraith menace?

Collecting SPACEKNIGHTS (2000) #3-4.
name: Redemption!
